contextNodes.label: Daytona
contextNodes.description: Cloud-native development environment platform that provides secure, isolated sandbox environments for code execution and development. Offers CLI tools, web dashboard, and SDKs for managing containerized development workspaces with snapshot capabilities and real-time collaboration features.
contextNodes.stats: Primarily Go-based backend services with TypeScript/React frontend, Python/Ruby/Go SDKs, and Astro documentation site
contextNodes.purpose: Enables developers to create, manage, and execute code in secure, isolated sandbox environments with persistent state and collaboration capabilities.

contextNodes.label: Developers
contextNodes.description: Software developers using the CLI tool to create sandboxes, execute code, manage Git repositories, and access LSP services for development workflows

contextNodes.label: End Users
contextNodes.description: Users accessing the React web dashboard via HTTPS to manage sandbox lifecycle, configure organization settings, and monitor sandbox operations

contextNodes.label: AI Systems
contextNodes.description: AI code generation systems using REST APIs and SDKs to programmatically create sandboxes, execute generated code, and manage development environments

contextNodes.label: Kafka Cluster
contextNodes.description: Apache Kafka message broker receiving audit logs and events via Kafka producer API using binary protocol over TCP

contextNodes.label: Redis Cache
contextNodes.description: Redis in-memory database providing caching, session storage, and pub/sub notifications via Redis client protocol (RESP)

contextNodes.label: Container Registry
contextNodes.description: OCI/Docker container registry storing sandbox base images accessed via Docker Registry HTTP API v2 over HTTPS

contextNodes.label: Cloud Storage
contextNodes.description: AWS S3 or compatible object storage for persistent file storage and snapshots accessed via S3 REST API over HTTPS

contextNodes.label: Observability Platform
contextNodes.description: External monitoring platforms receiving telemetry data via OpenTelemetry protocol (OTLP) over gRPC/HTTP

moduleNodes.label: telemetry-exporter
moduleNodes.description: Custom OpenTelemetry exporter that implements the OTLP (OpenTelemetry Protocol) interface to export traces, metrics, and logs from sandbox operations. Runs as a background worker process that batches telemetry data and forwards it to external observability platforms via HTTP/gRPC. Integrates with the OpenTelemetry Collector framework using Go's otelcol-core library and implements custom export logic for sandbox-specific metadata enrichment.
moduleNodes.architecture: Implements the OpenTelemetry Collector exporter interface pattern with a custom Go plugin that extends pdata.Traces, pdata.Metrics, and pdata.Logs types. Uses the collector's component.Component lifecycle for initialization and shutdown, with configurable batch processors for efficient data export. Follows the OTLP specification for data serialization and transport, supporting both HTTP and gRPC endpoints for downstream systems.
